===Alternative spellings===
* [[alledge]]

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/əˈlɛdʒ/}}, {{SAMPA|/@.lEdZ/}}
*: {{rhymes|ɛdʒ}}

===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|fro}} {{term|aleger}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|alleviare|alleviāre|lang=la}}, present active infinitive of {{term|allevio|alleviō|lighten|lang=la}}, from {{term|ad|lang=la}} + {{term|levis||light|lang=la}}.

====Verb====
{{en-verb|alleg|ing}}

# {{obsolete}} To [[lighten]], [[diminish]].
#* '''1485''', Sir Thomas Malory, ''Le Morte Darthur'', Book V:
#*: and suffir never your soveraynté to be '''alledged''' with your subjects, nother the soveraygne of your persone and londys.

===Etymology 2===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|aleggen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|xno}} {{term|aleger|lang=xno}}, the form from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|esligier|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|ML.}} *{{term||exlītigāre|to clear at law}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|ex||out}} + {{term|litigo|lītigō|sue at law|lang=la}}, the meaning from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|alleguer|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|allegare|allēgāre|lang=la}}, present active infinitive of {{term|allego|allēgō|send, depute; relate, mention, adduce|lang=la}}, from {{term|ad||to|lang=la}} + {{term|lego|lēgō|send|lang=la}}.

====Verb====
{{en-verb|alleg|ing}}

# {{transitive}} To make a [[claim]], a [[plea]] or offer [[justification]] for an act, especially before [[proof]] is available.
# {{transitive}} To make a [[statement]] under [[oath]].
# {{transitive}} To make a mere [[assertion]] without any [[proof]].
#: The [[agency]] '''alleged''' my [[credit]] history had problems.
# {{transitive}} To urge a reason or excuse
# {{archaic}} To [[cite]] or [[quote]] an author or his work ''for'' or ''against''.

